reviews.text:
Ordered laksa soup noodle with grill pork neck and hainam chicken with rice.
The laksa soap base was good and creamy, but the pork neck is served cold and the texture is weird. 
The hai nan chicken just like boil chicken without flavour. 
Average price and fine for a quick lunch.
Tried their shrimp laksa, soup is great, but the shrimps are not fresh.  Tables are quite packed.
Pretty good laska with Good soup.
dishes are tasty but not the noodle nor rice
點了兩個海南雞套餐$65@, 但每個套餐雞份量多,但係油飯好少, 要叫多一碗飯, 加多十二蚊, 而且店內近門口的位置基本上沒有冷氣,入少少就好啲,但都十分翳焗, 雖然有多把風扇,但感覺挺熱。

Food is delicious. Price is inexpensive.

The dinner set here was okay, priced at around hkd 58 to hkd 68, a drink is included. The curry beef is a bit less than I expected, the meat was not tender enough, but the sauce itself is good with not-too-strong curry taste. The soup provided is average, a good place to have a casual dinner alone or with family.
